[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]What impact will the devolution in 2015 of funding to Local Transport Bodies and the introduction of the Single Local Growth Fund have?
[normal]It will wipe out any consideration of sustainable transport schemes 
[normal]both 
[normal]big and small.   That is because it is designed to promote jobs
[normal] supported by road building
[normal].  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]However, the 
[normal]purpose
[normal] of creating employment is to increase the wealth and 
[normal]well being
[normal] of 
[normal]those in an area.  The cost 
[normal]/
[normal] benefit ratio of sustainable transport can bring significant economic benefits if factors, such as quality of life, well-being and basic health are admissible 
[normal]as equals in the discussion. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7
[normal]·
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]How can local 
[normal]authorities attract greater investment from the private sector for the delivery and maintenance of local transport infrastructure? What scope is there for the use of alternative funding streams?
[normal]No knowledge of this.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Existing funding streams need to be pr
[normal]otected as well as finding additional sources of funding. We have one example of a County Local Committee passing a motion to reallocate developer contributions away from sustainable transport.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
