[normal] 
[normal]How clear are the lines of accountability for
[normal] local decision making on transport expenditure?
[normal]The answer is that they are unclear to most.  But you must be more precise about what is meant by 'clear'.  It's an absolute term and when you factor in the implied 'clear to whom', then it's obvious that it
[normal] might be 100% clear to some 
[normal]- 
[normal]but 
[normal]unhelpfully 
[normal]opaque to others.  
[normal]So - please be 
[normal]less ambiguous
[normal].   But 
[normal]- 
[normal]of greater importance is whether local decision making is 
[normal]appropriate, relevant and worthwhile
[normal].   For example, it could be crystal clear but hopeless
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]inappropriate, irrelevant and worthless. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]It is 
[normal]absolutely 
[normal]not clear where accountability sits for the cycling elements of the West Sussex 
[normal]County Council 
[normal]Local Transport Plan 3 
[normal](LTP3) - 
[normal]and more specifically for cycling safety. 
[normal]  
[normal]Is it still a central res
[normal]ponsibility of the county council as the Highways Authority, or the County Local Committees, who control the key funding streams
[normal]; funding streams
[normal] that could be used to implement cycle schemes and improve cycling safety?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Submitted by 
[normal]Geoff Farrell, Chair of 
[normal]t
[normal]he West Sussex Cycle Forum (WSCF).   
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The WSCF was established to 
[normal]represent and support
[normal] the views of the various local cycling forums around the county. Whereas local cycle forums act locally and practically, the WSCF is a strateg
[normal]ic partner for the local forums and is recognised by West Sussex County Council as a 
[normal]consultee
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Its aim - as in its constitution is:
[normal]To work towards the creation of conditions in West Sussex so that cycling is perceived as a valid and reasonable choice of[bold] transport for both utility and leisure purposes.   [bold]&#xa0;
